## 💭 Retrospective

**Why Cloudflare Pages over GitHub Pages?** The core issue was the initial load experience. Static hosting forces a blank-page → JS language check → redirect cycle that causes a visible flicker. Edge Functions intercept the request before anything reaches the browser, so the first HTML is already correct.

**Why Svelte over Next.js?** Next.js static exports still ship the React runtime and incur hydration overhead — unnecessary for a content-focused portfolio. Svelte compiles components to optimized vanilla JS with no runtime, resulting in faster FCP and a smaller bundle.

**SEO vs. privacy tradeoff:** The Lighthouse SEO score of 66 is a deliberate choice. The résumé contains personal contact details and career history that shouldn't be freely indexed. `noindex` is the right call here.
